ActivityCommentText: SCR at baseflow, sedimentation has occurred in channel. Scouring has occurred since last visit. Lower banks have watercress, speedwell. Upper/floodplain covered in monkey flower. Lots of trash in reach, small plastics in channel. Large tire at bottom, metal axel at top of reach. Cow pies in stream channel, tire tracks as well. Large cottonwoods are predominant along with seep willows, 3 size classes each. Dragonfly and Damselfly nymphs. Lots of sand when trying to collect bug sample. Tried to get cladophora attached to rocks into algae sample. Used turkey baster to collect chl-a sample from composite bottle. Highly embedded C channel, stable.--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Yes; Normal Flow

ActivityCommentText: THIS C5 STREAM HAS A GREAT RIPARIAN OVERSTORY, BUT NO REGENERATION OF WOODY SPECIES. BANKS ARE STABLE AND WELL VEGETATED BUT THERE ARE EXCESS BARS (SIDE & MIDCHANNEL) AND SAND DOMINATED SUBSTRATE THROUGHOUT REACH. MACROPHYTES ARE DIVERSE AND ABUNDANT ALONG BOTH BANKS. ANOXIC SEDIMENTS AND ALGAE ALSO ALONG EDGES, BUT THERE ARE NO REAL POOLS. BUG DIVERSITY IS POOR; NO EPT, SNAILS PRESENT ALONG WITH BEETLES, MIDGES, DRAGON & DAMSELFLIES. MINIMAL RIFFLE HABITAT. SEWAGE SMELL. CHLORINE METER NOT FUNCTIONAL-NOT MEASURED.. Approved status: PATTI SPINDLER 21-JUL-11 12:00:00--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Migrated
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Station Description: SANTA CRUZ RIVER AT SANTA GERTRUDIS LANE Station Name: SANTA CRUZ RIVER - AT SANTA GERTRUDIS LANE

ActivityCommentText: SANTA CRUZ RIVER IS AT BASEFLOW, CLEAR WITH LOTS OF MACROPHYTES LIVING ON BANKS AND AGOSIA REDS AT MARGINS. APPEARS SAME AS LAST YEAR. RIPARIAN VEG STABILIZES BANKS AND FLOODPLAIN. MOSTLY COTTONWOOD- WILLOW. NO TAMARISK HERE. BANKS STABLE, NO EROSION. LOTS OF BARS WITHIN ACTIVE CHANNEL = OVERLOADING OF SEDIMENT AND POOR SCORES. SOME PFANKUCH AND PKC PARAMETERS. FEW C-W SAPLINGS ON BARS, MACROPHYTE BEDS LINE STREAM MARGINS BUT VERY FEW FINE (SILT/CLAY) SEDS. HABITAT 80% RUN WITH SAND AND GRAVELS = POOR BUG HABITAT. FEW COBBLES ON RIFFLES AND EDGE VEG = HABITAT FOR BUGS WHICH CONSIST OF 3 SPP. DRAGONFLIES, MAYFLIES, BEETLES. ALGAE = ALL CLADOPHORA, DIATOM COVER VISIBLE - BROWN BIOFILM. NO CRAYFISH. AGOSIA ABUNDANT. 1 LEOPARD FROG.. Approved status: PATTI SPINDLER 10-JUN-16 12:00:00--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Migrated

ActivityCommentText: SCR at baseflow, sedimentation has occurred in channel. Scouring has occurred since last visit. Lower banks have watercress, speedwell. Upper/floodplain covered in monkey flower. Lots of trash in reach, small plastics in channel. Large tire at bottom, metal axel at top of reach. Cow pies in stream channel, tire tracks as well. Large cottonwoods are predominant along with seep willows, 3 size classes each. Dragonfly and Damselfly nymphs. Lots of sand when trying to collect bug sample. ActivityCommentText: WE RELOCATED SITE FROM CHAVEZ SIDING RD CROSSING TO SANTA GERTRUDIS LN BECAUSE OF NEWLY POSTED NO TRESPASS SIGNS AND FENCING AT FORMER SITE. THERE IS APPROX 100M REACH BETWEEN FENCELINES WITH NATIONAL PARK SERVICE LAND AT NORTH END AND PRIVATE AT SOUTH END. WE SAMPLED THIS ENTIRE REACH FOR PEBBLE COUNT/VEG SURVEY. WATER SAMPLE WAS COLLECTED AT UPSTREAM END ABOVE ROAD CROSSING. SUBSTRATE MOSTLY SAND/GRAVEL WITH SILT/CLAY ALONG EDGES AND LOTS OF MACROPHYTES AND ALGAE THRUOUT. ADWR GUY SAID THAT MEXICO PLANS TO KEEP 1/3 OF WATER THEY WILL TREAT; COULD CAUSE OUR PART OF SCR TO GO DRY!. Approved status: PATTI SPINDLER 11-JUL-11 12:00:00--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Migrated

ActivityCommentText: SANTA CRUZ RIVER IS AT BASEFLOW, CLEAR WITH LOTS OF MACROPHYTES LIVING ON BANKS AND AGOSIA REDS AT MARGINS. APPEARS SAME AS LAST YEAR. RIPARIAN VEG STABILIZES BANKS AND FLOODPLAIN. MOSTLY COTTONWOOD- WILLOW. NO TAMARISK HERE. BANKS STABLE, NO EROSION. LOTS OF BARS WITHIN ACTIVE CHANNEL = OVERLOADING OF SEDIMENT AND POOR SCORES. SOME PFANKUCH AND PKC PARAMETERS. FEW C-W SAPLINGS ON BARS, MACROPHYTE BEDS LINE STREAM MARGINS BUT VERY FEW FINE (SILT/CLAY) SEDS. HABITAT 80% RUN WITH SAND AND GRAVELS = POOR BUG HABITAT. FEW COBBLES ON RIFFLES AND EDGE VEG = HABITAT FOR BUGS WHICH CONSIST OF 3 SPP. DRAGONFLIES, MAYFLIES, BEETLES. ALGAE = ALL CLADOPHORA, DIATOM COVER VISIBLE - BROWN BIOFILM. NO CRAYFISH. AGOSIA ABUNDANT. 1 LEOPARD FROG.. Approved status: PATTI SPINDLER 10-JUN-16 12:00:00--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Migrated
